{"GUID":"7959957e-c751-4fd4-896f-ffd482d10e80","Type":"Text","Text":"JOEL CHRISTNER JOEL CHRISTNER 1264 N MONROE ST SAN JOSE, CA 95128 (408) 396-3007 CELLULAR JOEL.CHRISTNER@GMAIL.COM
OBJECTIVE Highly-skilled, proven professional, published author seeking executive product management, marketing, or technology-centric position that requires expert-level technical proficiency, managerial experience, marketing know-how, and business acumen. Proven success with products focusing on data networking, storage networking, WAN optimization, application acceleration, distributed computing, content protection, and data classification. Extremely proficient in dissecting markets, understanding requirements, translating into product requirements, and executing aggressively to achieve results. Strong ability to brainstorm and implement future product direction and strategy. Very effective oral and written communicator with ability to present to very large and diverse audiences.
PROFESSIONAL EXPERIENCE 7/2007 – Present Reconnex Corporation Director, Product Management
www.reconnex.net Mountain View, CA
Responsible for establishing and maintaining entire corporate product line strategy, go-to-market, positioning, and sales enablement for a powerful family of content analysis, classification, and protection products. Key contributor to establishing company presence as a market leader, including analyst firms such as Gartner and Forrester. Helped to increase revenue by 50% quarter-over-quarter and over 200% year-over-year, and increase competitive win rate from 50% to 75% • Managed all aspects of product management for three diverse products (designed for different buyers) while providing solution consistency and integration (network focus, storage focus, and desktop focus) using value-based and solution-oriented sales tools. Successfully moved the company from a technical sales model to a solution sales model • Drove tactical and strategic requirements with engineering through numerous interactions with early adopters and ‘main street’ decision makers. Prioritized product requirements to quickly reach a point of competitive parity on foundational components and leadership for components that would be needed by next-generation data loss prevention (DLP) systems • Developed go-to-market strategy with key channel partners and OEMs to increase market presence and paths to market • Led the creation of sales and technical collateral for field and customer consumption, including data sheets, whitepapers, presentations, competitive analysis, use cases, solutions guides, and quick start guides. Also managed the creation, delivery, and messaging of product documentation, release notes, and online help systems to influence user perception of the product through its deployment lifecycle • Operationalized a streamlined system of collaboration amongst company units (sales, marketing, engineering, manufacturing) by implementing a Wiki, provided ongoing system management
12/2002 – 7/2007 Cisco Systems, Inc. Consistently rated top-10% employee 4/2006 – 7/2007 Senior Manager, Technical Marketing, Application Delivery Business Unit
www.cisco.com San Jose, CA
Responsible for providing product leadership, technical product line management, and strategic direction for application acceleration and WAN optimization products, including Cisco Wide Area Application Services (WAAS). Instrumental in helping build a $150M/yr business from the ground up in 9 months by leading an international and cross-functional team of professionals while also participating as a senior individual contributor (technical product line manager for the application delivery portfolio). Responsibilities and achievements include: • Led a cross-functional, cross-business unit task force to define the end-to-end architectural strategy for application delivery. Managed a global team of ten technical marketing engineers (TMEs) on tactical and strategic goals centered around sales enablement, technical leadership, and product line strategy • Technical leadership in end-to-end system design and roadmap development across multiple lines of business – including branch, WAN, and data center components. Key technical contributor to requirements and definition of technologies such as data suppression, compression, TCP optimization, application-specific acceleration, server offload, security, and platform technologies • Marketing leadership (internal and external) – developed high quality content for internal and external marketing purposes (data sheets, whitepapers, competitive analysis, feature briefs, performance briefs, solution briefs, knowledge portal). Delivered presentations at trade events and conferences such as Cisco Networkers and EMC Technology Summit. Systematically dismantled competitive products to identify weakness, increase sales competitive posture, and improve our own product offering • Empowering a geographically distributed team – providing guidance and leadership to align global technical marketing resources to business initiatives to drive productivity, revenue, and market impact
11/2004 – 4/2006 Senior Technical Marketing Engineer, Application Delivery Business Unit
San Jose, CA
Responsible for providing product line technical leadership, strategic direction, design guidance, competitive and market analysis, and field-facing and internal-facing marketing materials for Cisco application delivery products and technologies. Lead team member, guiding global team of TMEs supporting marketing, engineering, and research initiatives focused on Cisco Wide Area Application Services (WAAS) v4.0. Major accomplishments include: • Authored system design specifications for ADBU branch and WAN products, including Cisco WAFS, ACNS, and WAAS • Product launch – successfully drove the internal and external launch of products such as the FS Family of Integrated NAS, WAFS v3, and WAAS v4 • Sales enablement – including thorough competitive analysis, technical and sales whitepapers and presentations, knowledgebase management, design and support assistance for marquee customers • Internal and external marketing – speaking engagements in tradeshows, seminars, webinars, and internal TV broadcasts
Englewood, CO
12/2002 – 11/2004 Consulting Systems Engineer, Storage Networking Team
Provided storage and storage networking technical expertise to Cisco AM/SE account teams, VARs (Cisco and OEM), and OEM account teams within a geography covering six states on the Cisco MDS 9000 family of multilayer directors and fabric switches. Designed numerous customer solutions involving Fibre Channel, iSCSI, NAS, FCIP, and iSCSI using a unified and converged network fabric. • Drove storage revenue from zero to over $10M annually in a two year period • Channel training – developed technical and sales advocates through partner/OEM training events • SE leadership awards in both 2003 and 2004, including SE of the Year (2004) and SE of the Quarter (twice)
Senior Systems Engineer Chicago, IL Systems Engineer Chicago, IL Network Consultant Springfield, IL
5/2002 – 12/2002 Technology Exchange Inc www.tech-exchange.com 6/2001 – 1/2002 Solution Technology Inc. www.logicalis.com 6/1998 – 6/2001 Levi, Ray, and Shoup, Inc. www.lrs.com
AREAS OF EXPERTISE Concepts Distributed Computing OS Architecture Quality of Service Internet Protocols Application Acceleration Security
Routing and Switching Architecture Transport Protocol Architecture Storage and Data Center Infrastructure
Certifications Cisco Certified Internetwork Expert – Storage Area Networking, CCIE #15311 Cisco Certified Network Professional and Design Professional (CCNP, CCDP) Microsoft Certified Professional (MCP 2003), Microsoft Certified Systems Engineer (NT4, 2K) Brocade Certified Fabric Professional (BCFP)
PUBLICATIONS, PRESS, AND SPEAKING 2/2008 Deploying Cisco Wide Area Application Services (Book, 600pp)
Cisco Press
7/2007 Application Acceleration and WAN Optimization Fundamentals (Book, 400pp)
Cisco Press
2005-2006 EMC Technology Summit Presentations on infrastructure consolidation, and application acceleration
2005-2006 Cisco Networkers Live Numerous presentations on data center infrastructure, application acceleration, and WAN optimization. Recorded top five percent score for entire event both years.
Miscellaneous Numerous whitepapers and articles in well-known publications including Network World, SC Magazine, ESS
EDUCATION 1/2007 - Present Columbia University www.columbia.edu New York City, NY Enrolled Master of Science, Computer Science (Telecommunications Focus). Expected graduation end 2008. 6/1995 – 6/1998 DeVRY University www.dpg.devry.edu Addison, IL Completed Graduated with a Bachelor of Science degree in Electronics Engineering Technology.

{"model":"all-minilm","input":["JOEL CHRISTNER JOEL CHRISTNER 1264 N MONROE ST SAN JOSE, CA 95128 (408) 396-3007 CELLULAR JOEL.CHRISTNER@GMAIL.COM
OBJECTIVE Highly-skilled, proven professional, published author seeking executive product management, marketing, or technology-centric position that requires expert-level technical proficiency, managerial experience, marketing know-how, and business acumen. Proven success with products focusing on data networking, storage networking, WAN optimization, application acceleration, distributed computing, content protection, and data classification. Extremely proficient in dissecting markets, understanding requirements, translating into product requirements, and executing aggressively to achieve results. Strong ability to brainstorm and implement future product direction and strategy. Very effective oral and written communicator with ability to present to very large and diverse audiences.
PROFESSIONAL EXPERIENCE 7/2007 – Present Reconnex Corporation Director, Product Management
www.reconnex",".net Mountain View, CA
Responsible for establishing and maintaining entire corporate product line strategy, go-to-market, positioning, and sales enablement for a powerful family of content analysis, classification, and protection products. Key contributor to establishing company presence as a market leader, including analyst firms such as Gartner and Forrester. Helped to increase revenue by 50% quarter-over-quarter and over 200% year-over-year, and increase competitive win rate from 50% to 75% • Managed all aspects of product management for three diverse products (designed for different buyers) while providing solution consistency and integration (network focus, storage focus, and desktop focus) using value-based and solution-oriented sales tools. Successfully moved the company from a technical sales model to a solution sales model • Drove tactical and strategic requirements with engineering through numerous interactions with early adopters and ‘main street’ decision makers. Prioritized product requirements to quickly reach a point of competitive"," parity on foundational components and leadership for components that would be needed by next-generation data loss prevention (DLP) systems • Developed go-to-market strategy with key channel partners and OEMs to increase market presence and paths to market • Led the creation of sales and technical collateral for field and customer consumption, including data sheets, whitepapers, presentations, competitive analysis, use cases, solutions guides, and quick start guides. Also managed the creation, delivery, and messaging of product documentation, release notes, and online help systems to influence user perception of the product through its deployment lifecycle • Operationalized a streamlined system of collaboration amongst company units (sales, marketing, engineering, manufacturing) by implementing a Wiki, provided ongoing system management
12/2002 – 7/2007 Cisco Systems, Inc. Consistently rated top-10% employee 4/2006 – 7/2007 Senior Manager, Technical Marketing, Application Delivery Business Unit
www.cisco",".com San Jose, CA
Responsible for providing product leadership, technical product line management, and strategic direction for application acceleration and WAN optimization products, including Cisco Wide Area Application Services (WAAS). Instrumental in helping build a $150M/yr business from the ground up in 9 months by leading an international and cross-functional team of professionals while also participating as a senior individual contributor (technical product line manager for the application delivery portfolio). Responsibilities and achievements include: • Led a cross-functional, cross-business unit task force to define the end-to-end architectural strategy for application delivery. Managed a global team of ten technical marketing engineers (TMEs) on tactical and strategic goals centered around sales enablement, technical leadership, and product line strategy • Technical leadership in end-to-end system design and roadmap development across multiple lines of business – including branch, WAN, and data center components. Key technical contributor to requirements and definition of technologies such as data suppression, compression,"," TCP optimization, application-specific acceleration, server offload, security, and platform technologies • Marketing leadership (internal and external) – developed high quality content for internal and external marketing purposes (data sheets, whitepapers, competitive analysis, feature briefs, performance briefs, solution briefs, knowledge portal). Delivered presentations at trade events and conferences such as Cisco Networkers and EMC Technology Summit. Systematically dismantled competitive products to identify weakness, increase sales competitive posture, and improve our own product offering • Empowering a geographically distributed team – providing guidance and leadership to align global technical marketing resources to business initiatives to drive productivity, revenue, and market impact
11/2004 – 4/2006 Senior Technical Marketing Engineer, Application Delivery Business Unit
San Jose, CA
Responsible for providing product line technical leadership, strategic direction, design guidance, competitive and market analysis, and field-facing and internal-facing marketing materials for Cisco application delivery products and technologies."," Lead team member, guiding global team of TMEs supporting marketing, engineering, and research initiatives focused on Cisco Wide Area Application Services (WAAS) v4.0. Major accomplishments include: • Authored system design specifications for ADBU branch and WAN products, including Cisco WAFS, ACNS, and WAAS • Product launch – successfully drove the internal and external launch of products such as the FS Family of Integrated NAS, WAFS v3, and WAAS v4 • Sales enablement – including thorough competitive analysis, technical and sales whitepapers and presentations, knowledgebase management, design and support assistance for marquee customers • Internal and external marketing – speaking engagements in tradeshows, seminars, webinars, and internal TV broadcasts
Englewood, CO
12/2002 – 11/2004 Consulting Systems Engineer, Storage Networking Team
Provided storage and storage networking technical expertise to Cisco AM/SE account teams,"," VARs (Cisco and OEM), and OEM account teams within a geography covering six states on the Cisco MDS 9000 family of multilayer directors and fabric switches. Designed numerous customer solutions involving Fibre Channel, iSCSI, NAS, FCIP, and iSCSI using a unified and converged network fabric. • Drove storage revenue from zero to over $10M annually in a two year period • Channel training – developed technical and sales advocates through partner/OEM training events • SE leadership awards in both 2003 and 2004, including SE of the Year (2004) and SE of the Quarter (twice)
